<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Impotent" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Impotent,</orth> 1) weak, feeble: <cit><quote>i. and snail-paced beggary,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 3, 53</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lame and i. conclusion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 162</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) infirm, languishing under disease: <cit><quote>enforce the pained i. to smile,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.864" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 864</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>i. and bed-rid,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 29</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>